const abstractEN = [
  FH1("Abstract"),
  P("Egypt generates on the order of one hundred million tonnes of solid waste each year and, despite rapid recent progress, still fails to recover a large fraction of its recyclable beverage containers. The evidence from deposit-return countries such as Germany and Norway — where container-return rates exceed ninety-five per cent — shows that the decisive missing ingredient is not public awareness but an immediate, tangible reward for returning each container, a reward layer that Egypt currently lacks because it has neither national deposit legislation nor the barcode infrastructure such schemes require."),
  P("This project, Keep It Green, supplies that missing reward layer using artificial intelligence rather than legislation. It couples an AI-powered reverse-vending machine with a mobile reward application, a web dashboard, an on-machine kiosk, and a secure cloud backend. A user pairs their phone with the machine using an ATM-style six-digit code; a camera on the machine runs a YOLOv8 object-detection model that classifies each inserted item as a plastic bottle or an aluminium can; an Arduino opens the correct sorting compartment; and reward points are credited to the paired user instantly through the authenticated backend, later redeemable for partner-vendor offers."),
  P("The detector was trained on a unified dataset of 11,897 real-box images fused from four public detection datasets and achieves a mean Average Precision (mAP@0.5) of 0.928 on a held-out test set — exceeding the 0.90 target — while running well within the one-second real-time budget. The complete system was deployed publicly over HTTPS and validated end-to-end with forty-eight automated checks (23 core, 12 administrative, 13 multi-user isolation), all passing. This document describes the motivation, analysis, design, implementation, testing, and deployment of every part of the system in detail."),
  new Paragraph({ spacing: { before: 120 }, children: [run("Keywords: ", { bold: true }), run("reverse vending, object detection, YOLOv8, recycling incentives, .NET, Flutter, Arduino, Internet of Things, circular economy.", { i: true })] }),
];
